---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="Pranika Jain — engineer of ten years, now in the open space between that and whatever comes next."
>
  <article class="mx-auto max-w-page px-5 py-16 sm:px-8 sm:py-24">
    {/* Header eyebrow only */}
    <p
      class="flex items-center gap-3 font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.3em] text-terracotta-600 dark:text-terracotta-300"
    >
      <svg viewBox="0 0 16 16" aria-hidden="true" class="h-3 w-3">
        <path
          d="M8,1 C9,5 11,7 15,8 C11,9 9,11 8,15 C7,11 5,9 1,8 C5,7 7,5 8,1 Z"
          fill="currentColor"
        ></path>
      </svg>
      About
    </p>

    {/* Title + bio share a column on the left; portrait sits to the right,
        top-aligned with the h1. Bio flows immediately under the h1 — no
        gap forced by the photo height. */}
    <div class="mt-3 grid gap-10 sm:grid-cols-[1fr_auto] sm:items-start">
      <div>
        <h1
          class="font-display text-4xl leading-[1.05] tracking-tight text-ink sm:text-6xl dark:text-cream"
        >
          <span class="italic text-terracotta-600 dark:text-terracotta-300"
            >Hi</span
          >, I'm Pranika.
        </h1>

        {/* Bio — Pranika's voice, verbatim. */}
        <section
          class="prose prose-lg mt-6 max-w-prose font-display text-ink prose-p:font-sans prose-p:text-lg prose-p:leading-relaxed prose-p:text-ink-soft sm:prose-p:text-xl dark:prose-invert dark:text-cream dark:prose-p:text-cream-soft"
        >
      {/* Bio — kept in sync with public/aboutme/about.txt (source of truth). */}
      <p>
        I grew up in Delhi sketching whatever I was feeling, a habit that
        quietly turned my notebooks into a decade-long visual diary, where
        each page is still vivid in my memory. I studied computer science,
        then spent ten years as a software engineer. I'm now in the open
        space between that and whatever comes next.
      </p>
      <p>
        When I was a kid, every adult who met me and my brother delivered
        the same verdict: &ldquo;Pranav, so innocent. Pranika, so
        naughty.&rdquo; I had usually done nothing. I never quite figured
        out how they were so sure. Then my niece arrived, with those same
        eyes, and got accused of mischief for the crime of sitting on a
        couch. I watched it happen and felt something close to delight. I
        wouldn't trade it now.
      </p>
      <p>
        I notice people inside their small joys. A kid losing it at a candy
        store. A mother dancing with her baby in the corner of a wedding.
        Two people meeting at airport arrivals after years apart, and the
        half-second before they reach each other. Most of my favorite
        moments belong to other people; I'm just lucky enough to be in the
        room. Lately I've started carrying a camera too. 
      </p>
      <p>
        For years, I've collected magents from every place I've been (only
        the strange three-dimensional ones; flat ovals get nothing from me).
        I enjoy cooking something I've never made before, occasionally,
        ambitiously, and being genuinely surprised when it works on the
        first try.I once jumped out of a plane over Key West and couldn't
        stop thinking about it for months.
      </p>
      {/* Closing line — mobile only; on sm+ it lives under the portrait
          in the right column with its own centered display style. */}
      <p class="sm:hidden">
        In a world where you can be anything, I try to be{' '}
        <em class="text-terracotta-600 dark:text-terracotta-300">kind</em>.
      </p>
        </section>
      </div>

      {/* Portrait + closing line — right column, desktop only. On
          mobile the photo is dropped and the closing line is rendered
          inline with the bio above (see the sm:hidden paragraph). */}
      <div class="hidden w-40 flex-col items-center gap-6 sm:flex sm:w-52">
        <img
          src="/images/profile/avatar.jpg"
          alt="Pranika — black-and-white portrait, smiling at the camera"
          width="1100"
          height="1956"
          loading="eager"
          class="aspect-[4/5] w-full rounded-2xl object-cover object-top shadow-soft ring-1 ring-ink/10 dark:ring-cream/10"
        />

        {/* Small hand-drawn flourish */}
        <div aria-hidden="true" class="flex items-center justify-center gap-2">
          <span class="h-px w-8 bg-ink/20 dark:bg-cream/20"></span>
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 12" class="h-3 w-6 text-terracotta-500">
            <path
              d="M1,6 Q4,1 8,6 T16,6 T23,6"
              fill="none"
              stroke="currentColor"
              stroke-width="1.2"
              stroke-linecap="round"
            ></path>
          </svg>
          <span class="h-px w-8 bg-ink/20 dark:bg-cream/20"></span>
        </div>

        <p
          class="text-balance text-center font-display text-base leading-snug text-ink-soft dark:text-cream-soft"
        >
          In a world where you can be anything, I try to be
          <em
            class="font-display text-terracotta-600 dark:text-terracotta-300"
            >kind</em
          >.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    {/* Currently */}
    <section class="mt-20 border-t border-ink/10 pt-10 dark:border-cream/10">
      <h2
        class="font-display text-2xl text-ink sm:text-3xl dark:text-cream"
      >
        <span class="italic">Currently</span>
      </h2>
      <dl
        class="mt-6 grid gap-x-10 gap-y-5 sm:grid-cols-[8rem_1fr] sm:items-baseline"
      >
        <dt
          class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-terracotta-600 dark:text-terracotta-300"
        >
          Reading
        </dt>
        <dd class="font-sans text-ink-soft dark:text-cream-soft/85">
          <em class="font-display">The Black Swan</em> by Nassim Nicholas Taleb
        </dd>

        <dt
          class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-terracotta-600 dark:text-terracotta-300"
        >
          Cooking
        </dt>
        <dd class="font-sans text-ink-soft dark:text-cream-soft/85">
          <em class="font-display">Massaman Curry</em> and
          <em class="font-display">Afghani Paneer</em>
        </dd>

      </dl>
    </section>

    {/* Contact */}
    <section class="mt-20 border-t border-ink/10 pt-10 dark:border-cream/10">
      <h2
        class="font-display text-2xl text-ink sm:text-3xl dark:text-cream"
      >
        <span class="italic">Say</span> hi
      </h2>
      <dl
        class="mt-6 grid gap-x-10 gap-y-5 sm:grid-cols-[8rem_1fr] sm:items-baseline"
      >
        <dt
          class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-terracotta-600 dark:text-terracotta-300"
        >
          LinkedIn
        </dt>
        <dd class="font-sans text-ink-soft dark:text-cream-soft/85">
          <a
            href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/pranika-jain-77b470107/"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noreferrer noopener"
            class="link-wobble"
            >linkedin.com/in/pranika-jain</a
          >
        </dd>
      </dl>
    </section>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
